Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
Every coin has two sides. Freshman are not very familiar with the new environment so it is safer for them to live on campus. Also, the first year of college requires a lot of social activities, it is a time when people starts to know each other. It would be better if they all live close to each other and spend more time with each other.

The other part might be the rooms are small and the facilities might not be as good as off campus housing. people also need to share room with others which means they don't have much private space.